# Learned Patterns: Go

Auto-generated from 2 incidents in hippocampus.

## 1. ERROR: goroutine leak: http.Client without timeout causes goroutine to hang forever on slow responses
CONTEXT: Building HTTP client for Ollama LLM provider
ROOT CAUSE: Created http.Client{} without setting Timeout field. Default is no timeout, so any slow/hanging server causes permanent goroutine leak.
FIX: Always create http.Client with explicit timeout: &http.Client{Timeout: 30 * time.Second}
PREVENTION: Never use http.Client{} without Timeout. Always set Timeout or use context with deadline.
FILE: internal/adapter/llm/provider.go

## 2. CRITICAL BUG: Production crash in hippocampus MCP server. Fatal panic in goroutine during concurrent recall — data race on working memory map. Root cause: missing mutex lock in WorkingMemory.Snapshot(). The crash caused data loss of 3 session summaries. Emergency rollback deployed.

